	abstract="We study finite groups G having a non-trivial, proper subgroup H and {\$}{\$}D {\backslash}subset G {\{}{\backslash}setminus {\}} H, D {\backslash}cap D^{\{}-1{\}}={\backslash}emptyset ,{\$}{\$}D⊂G{\backslash}H,D∩D-1=∅,such that the multiset {\$}{\$}{\backslash}{\{} xy^{\{}-1{\}}:x,y {\backslash}in D{\backslash}{\}}{\$}{\$}{\{}xy-1:x,y∈D{\}}has every non-identity element occur the same number of times (such a D is called a difference set). We show that {\$}{\$}|G|=|H|^2{\$}{\$}|G|=|H|2, and that {\$}{\$}|D {\backslash}cap Hg|=|H|/2{\$}{\$}|D∩Hg|=|H|/2for all {\$}{\$}g {\backslash}notin H{\$}{\$}g∉H. We show that H is contained in every normal subgroup of index 2, and other properties. We give a 2-parameter family of examples of such groups. We show that such groups have Schur rings with four principal sets, and that, further, these difference sets determine DRADs.",
